First followed CSR generation instructions here: https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/csr

focoto.orig.key - This is just a private key, with a simple password
focoto.key - This is just focoto.orig.key with the password removed
focoto.csr - The certificate signing request created for www.focoto.com

The CSR was pasted into a web form and used to generate the intermediate and site keys.
RapidSSL emailed the following:

ssl_site_key.crt - The "Web Site Certificate"
ssl_intermediate_key.pen - The "Intermediate Certificate" (root certificate?)

The above site and intermediate certificates were combined according to:
https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/ssl-certificate

ssl_final.crt - The final, real, certificate that is combined with focoto.key
to be used on the server according to to for://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/ssl#acquirecert
